turnkey-valkey-19.0 (1) turnkey; urgency=medium

  * Port base to Debian 13 (Trixie) for TurnKey v19.
  * Install valkey-server from Trixie via plan/main; remove Bookworm backports script.
  * Security: Trixie currently ships valkey-server 8.1.1+dfsg1-3, which predates upstream
    Lua CVE fixes (CVE-2025-49844, -46817, -46818, -46819). Upgrade once
    Trixie publishes a fixed package; if v19 releases first, a temporary
    upstream build may be used in the interim.

 -- Parker Shankin-Clarke <parkerwsc1@gmail.com>  Tue, 07 Oct 2025 00:00:00 +0000

turnkey-valkey-18.1 (1) turnkey; urgency=low

  * Initial Valkey appliance based on TurnKey Redis app.
    - Installs valkey-server from Debian bookworm-backports
    - Includes Redis Commander UI behind Nginx/PM2 (HTTPS :443)
    - Inithooks wire Valkey requirepass + RC backend password on first boot

